Financing Options for Homes Under $400K

One of the biggest misconceptions:
You need massive savings.

In reality, many buyers use:

FHA Loans
	•	3.5% down payment
	•	Flexible credit thresholds
	•	Popular with first-time buyers

Conventional 3% Down Programs
	•	Lower mortgage insurance in some cases
	•	Competitive for strong credit profiles

Florida Assistance Programs

Income-based programs may assist with upfront costs depending on eligibility.

Example:

On a $375K home:
	•	3% down = $11,250
	•	3.5% down = $13,125

Many buyers are closer than they think.

